===Initialisation===

===Etymology===
An acronymn for the [[gaelic]] Radio Telefís Éireann, or in English "Irish TV and Radio". 

===Proper Noun===
'''RTÉ'''
The state broadcaster of the [[Republic of Ireland]]. It currently runs a [[32 county]] service of three TV channels, and four radio services, in both [[English]] & [[Irish]]. It is funded from both a licence fee and commercial advertising.


